	<div class="container" id="description-template">
		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-md-2">
				<img class="logo img-responsive" src="${request.static_url('dbas:static/images/logo.png')}" alt="dbas logo">
			</div>
			<div class="col-md-10">
				<div class="content">
					<h2><span class="font-semi-bold">Description</span> <span class="smaller">of D-BAS</span></h2>

					<p class="lead">In the following a <span class="font-normal">short description</span> of D-BAS will be given with the help of bulletpoints:
						<ul class="lead list">
							<li> Participants are able to add and modify positions and arguments in every discussion.
								<li> Positions and arguments are connected logically by participants</li>
								<li> The system is very easy to use.</li>
								<li> It offers a time-shifted discussion in three modes:</li>
								<ul class="lead list">
									<li> Guided Discussion: The participants will be lead through the discussion .</li>
									<li> Island View: A position with all connected arguments is presented as island. This supports the insight of a discussion about a specific position.</li>
									<li> Expert View: Participants are able to see and do everything.</li>
								</ul>
								<li> Contributions can be rated by the participants.</li>
								<li> You have the huge power of the crowd!.</li>
						</ul>
						<br>
						<p class="lead">This sounds amazing, but every egg-laying, milk-bearing woolly sow has its beginning. Due to this the <span class="font-normal">first milesstone</span> contains:
							<ul class="lead list">
								<li> System is based on a finished argumentation map.</li>
								<li> A base form of the guided view will be avbailable:</li>
								<ul class="lead list">
									<li> The participant will be confronted with an argument out of the finished argumentation map.
									<li> He has several options to choose, so this will be a kind of led <a href="http://www.bpb.de/politik/wahlen/wahl-o-mat/" alt="Wahl-O-Mat">Wahl-O-Mat</a>.</li>
									<li> We will have no KI, recommender systems or predictions of the next post. Everything will be statically.
								</ul>
								<li> Participants will be tracked, but every data is accessible.</li>
								<li> Everything will be done with unit and integration tests.</li>
							</ul>
						</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="container" id="features-template">
		<div class="row">
			<div class="col-md-2">
				<img class="logo img-responsive" src="${request.static_url('dbas:static/images/logo.png')}" alt="dbas logo">
			</div>
			<div class="col-md-10">
				<div class="content">
					<h2><span class="font-semi-bold">Features</span> <span class="smaller">of D-BAS</span></h2>
					<p class="lead">This is about
						<span class="font-normal">... features ...</span>
					</p>
					<dl class="dl-horizontal lead list">
						<dt>ArguMaps:</dt>
						<dd>The datastructure is equivalent to a kind of argumentation map. It is like a mind map, but the relations between the nodes are highly important and can have several meanings.</dd>
						<dt>Dialogue-based:</dt>
						<dd>Even if the system uses an argumentation map</dd>
						<dt>Guided View:</dt>
						<dd> Explanation about the view. Der Benutzer wird mit ausgewählten Beiträgen der anderen Teilnehmer konfrontiert. Die Wahl des nächsten Beitrags ist Teil der Dissertation.</dd>
						<dt>Island View:</dt>
						<dd> Explanation about the view. Es werden sogenannte Inseln präsentiert, die aus einer Position und allen Argumenten geordnet als Pro/Kontra-Liste bestehen.</dd>
						<dt>Expert View:</dt>
						<dd> Explanation about the view. Der Benutzer erhält Einblick auf die gesamte Argumentation Map und kann sich frei bewegen. Darstellungsvariante ist noch offen (Liste, Baum, Graph, Container und/oder Matrix (siehe [SLPM10], S.12)).</dd>
					</dl>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>

